    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Cal Raleigh** stands as our premier offensive anchor with a score of 78.02. Despite facing a left-hander in Prielipp, **Cal Raleigh** benefits from a high-efficiency park factor and a spot batting second, where his projected xwOBA of 0.371 against this tier of pitching creates an elite efficiency ceiling. **Will Smith** also grades out as a strong play at 72.25; even with his lineup spot currently pending, the combination of a weak 4.64 xERA from Paddack and favorable wind conditions makes him a near-lock to provide production across the counting categories. While **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is facing a tougher southpaw in Matz, his base power projection is so high that he remains a staple of our lineup at 66.83, buoyed further by the favorable wind-out conditions at the park.\n\nWe are navigating significant regression risks with **Masyn Winn** and **Jonathan Aranda**, both of whom hover near the marginal threshold. **Masyn Winn** is being penalized by a -5% wind-in adjustment and a difficult matchup against Montgomery, M; while we value his potential for speed, his 41.45 efficiency score makes him a start only due to roster necessity. **Gavin Sheets** rounds out the lineup at 44.66, suffering from a dynamic platoon disadvantage against the lefty Boyd. Given the current roster structure, no bench players like **Lawrence Butler**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, or **Yainer Diaz** were available to displace these starters due to team off-days, forcing us to lean on the current active pool. Monitor the status of **Will Smith** and **Gavin Sheets** closely; should their lineup positions drift toward the bottom of the order, their efficiency scores will crater, potentially forcing a defensive substitution if we were not facing a league-wide shortage of available pivots today.",
